main event: A fast-moving unidentified object was observed near Charleston, West Virginia on May 4, 1966.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar by the Charleston-Kanawha County Airport at an estimated speed of 500 mph and an altitude of 25,000 ft.
The object made a tight left turn and disappeared from the radar scope.
A Beechcraft 95 aircraft, flight 543, reported seeing the object and was told to stand by while the radar operator checked with the controller, who confirmed there were no other aircraft in the area.
The radar operator reported the sighting to his controller and the civil defense director, who were both surprised and concerned.
The report indicates the investigation was not handled very carefully, and the witness felt the details of what he saw were not fully captured.
witnesses: radar operator at Charleston-Kanawha County Airport
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
